result.execSummary:
The defendant Myisha D Dixon was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Forgery-Uttering, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.38(2).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Myisha D Dixon in court with attorney Brent W. Varner.  Defendant Myisha D Dixon in custody.  Michael Albrecht appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State gives recommendation.  Plea to Count 1.   Attorney Varner agrees.  No contest Plea entered, advised of constitutional rights, plea accepted by Court.  Court finds Defendant guilty.  Court goes through constitutional rights with defendant.  Defendant agrees and understands.  Court confirms with Attorney Varner and defendant that a PSI is not requested to proceed today.  Defendant agrees and understands.  PSI waived.  Court imposes sentence.
Count 1:
$268.00 fine & $250.00 DNA costs & provide a sample, 60 days to pay or set up a payment plan.
9 months in Sauk County Jail, with huber. 41 days credit. Forthwith.  Consecutive to any other sentences.  
Paperwork handed in court.
